<h2>Things to do</h2>

<p>
  There’s a ton of things to do in Queenstown. There’s amazing scenery, great restaurants, shopping and more. Queenstown specialises in outdoor pursuits – hiking, mountain biking and the more adventurous things too. If you like excitement,
  Queenstown is the adventure capital of New Zealand! Alternatively you might prefer a winery tour – some of the country’s best vineyards surround the city, with the pinot noir grape growing especially well in the region’s tough climate. There’s everything
  in between as well.
</p>

<p>
  Check out https://www.queenstownnz.co.nz/information/thingstodo/ for a more comprehensive list.

N.B. Some activities – especially flights – are weather dependent. If you book ahead of time, operators will advise whether the activity will go ahead with 24 hours or less notice.
They should reschedule for you if the weather’s not favourable; but you must check this when you book. It’s wise to give yourself some flexibility with these types of events in case they need to be rescheduled.
As with any activities, there will be risks, so make sure you check out safety procedures and the operators before you book.
</p>
